<br>
You obviously are not reading the same thread as I am, very few have mentioned having an issue with your soloing for XPs.  The vast majority are concerned about your being able to solo named mobs meant of a group (which is really just a content fix), a small group using charm to take down events that normally would take many more players and the sheer strenght charm gives you as a damage dealer in groups.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>I for one enjoy soloing for exp now, raids consume 60% of my time.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Well who would not mind soloing for an AA every 20-30 minutes?!?  It seems a bit excessive to me but it really does not directly affect me either so I am not concerned with it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>I hate to draw attention to things that someone's gonna wanna nerf, but Necros went from 500dd nukes (Ignite/Incinerate bones.. not counting undead nukes.) to a 1500+ DD Nuke at 61.. that's a 300% increase in power. </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Actually you are incorrect.  First off SoE added the ancient:Lifebane at 60th level back in Luclin.  Then with PoP they added the 44th, 54th and 61st level verisons.  So our DD does not make a huge jump from 500ish to 1300 in PoP.<br>
<br>
Oh and Neurtoxin max's out at 1300 at 65th level, Lifebane is 1050.  So our DD potiental increased 250 points from Luclin to PoP, hardly +150%.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>If people want high level charm removed then Verant has to remove the entire spell line because from level 12 it must be overpowered. When I say the ratio between Luclin mobs that are charmable compared to the ones in POP, they are almost the same in terms of the ratio in both damage and HP.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I doubt anyone really thinks charm needs to be removed, that is just plan silly.  Charm is one of the core abilities of Chanters and it should remain a powerful YET dangerous ability.  The issue is not just the increase from Luclin to PoP mobs, it is the fac that no other class progressed an equal amount.<br>
<br>
Not to mention that at 60th level Chanters could not sustain a charm over a 60th level mob, they could over a mob 7 levels lower thou.  In PoP you can mantain a charm over a 65th level mob, which means a much, much more powerful mob then you could have with your lower level charm.<br>
