<br>
This is directed to you since you seem to be the main person claiming charm isn't broken.<br>
<br>
If Enchanters were given an addition spell to summon a pet that would have the stats equal to the best stat of any of the mages, would they use it to solo instead of charim.  <br>
<br>
I did't think so.<br>
<br>
How bout if you could summon a pet with stats 120% better.<br>
How bout if you could summon a pet with stats 140% better.<br>
How bout if you could summon a pet with stats 160% better.<br>
How bout if you could summon a pet with stats 200% better.<br>
How bout if you could summon a pet with stats 400% better<br>
How bout if you could summon a pet with stats 800% better.<br>
<br>
Since water pets do 50 - 75 DPS depending on position, that would be 400 - 600 DPS.  <br>
<br>
An enchanter would use charm until the pet was somewhere between 8 times to 10 times stronger than the best attributes of all the mages pets.  At this point, the strength of the pet starts to outweigh the disadvantages of random charm lenght.    <br>
<br>
Would mages be balanced if they had a pet 8 to 10 times stronger than they do now?? <br>
<br>
Enchanter have always been the main buffers/debuffers/crowd controllers of a group.  Sure, these functions can be replaced by two or more characters, but they will not do as well of a job and they take additonal spots in the group.  Enchanters are practically a required class in high level groups.  This has been true throughout all the expansions and especially true for POP.  <br>
<br>
Charm is so powerful that once they get it, enchanters stop forming groups.  Their either are soloing, two boxing with a cleric alt, or duoing with their cleric friends.  You claim that pet-centered groups are putting melees out of a job.  Look at the pet-centered posts.  They all start out &quot;we were looking for a group and could not get one formed.&quot; They could not get the group formed because there were NO SLOWERS. {Enchanters are soloing and shamans are in a group the second they show up in the zone}  It is the  enchanters outrageous solo ability due to charm that leaves melees with on one to group with.  Melee's are having such a problem finding groups, monks have started a thread to get mages a summoned slow so that groups can start.  {This probably won't work because a reliable summoned slow would greatly inprove mages solo ability and they would be soloing instead of LFG for long periods of time.}<br>
<br>
Charm in POP is broken.  It doesn't matter how much you deny it LordGojirax, or claim it isn't, it will be changed.  Sony can not allow all the melees to go LFG until they get frustated and quilt.  POP, as it is today, has nearly destroyed the causal player.  People who only have an hour or so to play, can't get groups and are going to quit.  Look at the number of threads where the casual players de-leveled back to 60 so they can go back to the old world because they are tired of LFG.  <br>
<br>
Sony has to get the enchanters back into groups or they are going to see a mass exodus of players that are not either an enchanter, a shaman, or a pet-class{Add a beastlord to an all mage group and they do ok}<br>
<br>
Enchanters had better start giving creative solutions to this problem instead of claiming it doesn't exist and belittling everyone who says it does or they are going to end up with charm that does work in POP at all.  <br>
<br>
I see 4 possible solutions to this problem:<br>
<br>
1.  Make POP mobs uncharmable or make it so that charms only works on a very small number of mobs. {Similar to the way charm that mages have works.}<br>
<br>
2.  Make it so that charmed mobs can't be recharmed or mezzed by the enchanter.  Charm can still be used, but they would want the group to handle the mob when the charm wears off or they would be zoning alot so their efficency would go way down and grouping would be a better option. <br>
<br>
3.  Limit the DPS and Hit points of a charmed mob to a certain level.  <br>
<br>
4.  Give the enchanters abilities to other classes as well so that groups can be formed and other classes can play in POP too.  {Mages get slow, Wizards get KEI, Monks get AC and HP buffs, druids get debuffs, Warriors get runes, rogues get mez, etc}  <br>
